WEBVTT

00:00:08.229 --> 00:00:11.354 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
OK, kids,
it’s time to practice our Bible books!

00:00:11.354 --> 00:00:13.479 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Are you ready to try some
of the Hebrew Scriptures?

00:00:13.479 --> 00:00:14.729 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Ready!

00:00:14.729 --> 00:00:19.687 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Genesis!
The book that tells how Paradise was lost.

00:00:19.687 --> 00:00:24.479 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Exodus!
God saved his people by his mighty hand.

00:00:24.479 --> 00:00:29.270 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Leviticus!
God’s laws to keep them holy day by day.

00:00:29.270 --> 00:00:34.187 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Numbers!
Some lost the chance to see the Promised Land.

00:00:34.187 --> 00:00:39.145 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Deuteronomy!
Encouragement to listen and obey.

00:00:39.145 --> 00:00:44.104 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Joshua!
Each family got a place to call their own.

00:00:44.104 --> 00:00:49.062 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Judges!
God’s mighty ones performing mighty deeds.

00:00:49.062 --> 00:00:53.812 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Ruth!
Rewarded with a family and a home.

00:00:53.812 --> 00:00:58.854 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
First Samuel!
God chooses faithful David to be king.

00:00:58.854 --> 00:01:03.812 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Second Samuel!
The trouble in his house because of sin.

00:01:03.812 --> 00:01:08.687 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
First Kings!
The kingdom is divided north and south.

00:01:08.687 --> 00:01:13.687 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Second Kings!
Though most were bad, a few were faithful men.

00:01:13.687 --> 00:01:18.229 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
First Chronicles!
The things they learned from lessons in the past.

00:01:18.229 --> 00:01:23.354 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Second Chronicles!
Bad rulers lead the nation to its fall.

00:01:23.354 --> 00:01:28.395 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Ezra!
His work restored true worship once again.

00:01:28.395 --> 00:01:33.229 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Nehemiah!
He helped rebuild the city and its walls.

00:01:33.229 --> 00:01:37.854 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Esther!
She spoke with courage when the time was right.

00:01:37.854 --> 00:01:43.062 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Job!
Integrity is precious in God’s eyes.

00:01:43.062 --> 00:01:48.020 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Psalms!
Inspired songs to praise God’s love and might.

00:01:48.020 --> 00:01:52.687 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Proverbs!
The wisdom of its words is always true.

00:01:52.687 --> 00:01:57.770 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Ecclesiastes!
The happiness that serving God will bring.

00:01:57.770 --> 00:02:02.729 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Song of Solomon!
True love is ever loyal, always strong.

00:02:02.729 --> 00:02:06.854 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Isaiah!
How life will be when Jesus rules as King.

00:02:06.854 --> 00:02:11.687 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The Bible
is the greatest book of all.

00:02:11.687 --> 00:02:16.562 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Jehovah
is its author, you’ll recall.

00:02:16.562 --> 00:02:21.645 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
Let’s read it ev’ry day,
to learn it and obey.

00:02:21.645 --> 00:02:25.895 line:90%,end position:50%,center align:center
The Bible
is the greatest book of all.

